data.name: Xatu

attacks.name: Psywave
attacks.text: Does 20 damage times the amount of Energy attached to the Defending Pokémon.

attacks.name: Confuse Ray
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

data.flavorText: In South America, it is said that its right eye sees the future and its left eye views the past.

abilities.name: Mirror Coat
abilities.text: If Xatu is Burned or Poisoned by an opponent's attack (even if Xatu is Knocked Out), the Attacking Pokémon is now affected by the same Special Conditions (1 if there is only 1).

attacks.name: Dazzle Dance
attacks.text: Each Defending Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Psyloop
attacks.text: Does 30 damage plus 30 more damage for each Trainer card your opponent has in play.

data.name: Xatu

attacks.name: Future Sight
attacks.text: Look at the top 5 cards of either player's deck and put them back on top of that player's deck in any order.

attacks.name: Stressful Eye
attacks.text: Your opponent reveals his or her hand. Discard a Trainer card you find there.

data.flavorText: They say that it stays still and quiet because it is seeing both the past and future at the same time.

abilities.name: Synchronicity
abilities.text: You may attach any Technical Machine to Xatu.

attacks.name: Warp Hole
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose a card from your discard pile and put it on top of your deck.

abilities.name: Extra Feather
abilities.text: Each of your Stage 2 Pokémon-ex does 10 more damage to the Defending Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

abilities.name: Psychic Shift
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if Xatu is on your Bench, you may choose 1 Special Condition from 1 of your Active Pokémon and remove that Special Condition. Then, 1 of the Defending Pokémon is now affected by that Special Condition that you chose.

attacks.name: Energy Singe
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each Energy attached to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.flavorText: This odd Pokémon can see both the past and the future. It eyes the sun's movement all day.
